Male genitalia (
Fig. 13
) general characters: paramere tips sagittate, distal ends and plsa sharply pointed, lateral margins emarginate, medial margins of distal ½ of tips parallel and nearly touching one another, only distal ½ of tips extending beyond aedeagus, in lateral view tips with emarginately arcuate ventral margin; basal piece large and long, almost as long as parameres; parameres with distinctive elongate pwsa on ventral surface.
